This restaurant is quite the disappointment. I came here because they serve Khao Soi for $9.50 during lunch time, which is much cheaper than other Thai restaurants in the area for this specific dish. It's a small restaurant with an outside patio, but the style is old as is the building.  The good: The Thai Ice Tea is good and refreshing. Servers are nice and welcoming.  The bad: The Khao Soi, which lists on their menu as a Traditional Northern Thai red curry egg noodles soup with chicken, topping with pickled cabbage, red onions, crispy noodles, and scallions, was the worst Khao Soi I've had. The egg noodle texture was the same as eating as ramen from a cup noodles, and the crispy noodles were basically fried wonton strips. There is hardly and chicken, and it is thinly sliced pieces of white meat chicken instead of chunks of dark meat chicken or a whole chicken leg.  Overall, I was highly disappointed in this restaurant, and the only highlight of the meal is the Thai Ice Tea. Perhaps their other dishes may taste better, but they should remove Khao Soi off their menu if they aren't going to serve it right.

Let me start off by saying that it's not BAD food per se, but it's not all that impressive, either.  Still, I've eaten there about 4-5 times until I went there with a group of seven people.  The service was very slow (but polite) considering there was only one other table of two people.  The bill (with tax) was $100 - quite affordable considering the size of the group.  We left an 18% tip (all on one card), and on our way out the server actually stopped us and demanded more.  We argued for a few minutes because he thought we left 10%, but it's not exactly rocket surgery to figure percentages when your bill is 100.  Long story short, I threw another five bucks on the table and told him I'm never going back.  What a silly way to eliminate repeat business.  I'll be going to one of the MANY other Dupont Thai places from now on.
